type="machine">#357</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-357.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>13</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="alex-nelson.xml"
addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>(1) The dihedral group describes the symmetries of the regular <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-gon in the plane, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is rotation anticlockwise by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[2\pi  / n]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> is reflection about a line through the origin.</fr:p>
<fr:p>(2) Some authors (like Dummit and Foote) call this group <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D_{2n}]]></fr:tex> because it is of <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-000P.xml"
addr="gr-000P"
title="Order of a group">order</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[2n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>(3) <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D_{1}]]></fr:tex> has <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x=1]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D_{0}]]></fr:tex> is degenerate.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
