type="local"
href="dummit-2004-abstract.xml"
addr="dummit-2004-abstract"
title="Abstract Algebra">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 1.5</fr:meta><fr:meta
name="source">Hungerford <fr:link
type="local"
href="hungerford-1974-algebra.xml"
addr="hungerford-1974-algebra"
title="Algebra">Algebra</fr:link> Exercise 1.2.3</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We may define the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Quaternion Group</html:dfn> as consisting of the set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Q_{8}=\{-1\}\cup \{i^{m}j^{n}k^{p}\mid  0\leq  m,n,p\leq  3\}]]></fr:tex> where we identify <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1=i^{0}j^{0}k^{0}]]></fr:tex> and it obeys the identities
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[i^{2}=j^{2}=k^{2}=ijk=-1]]></fr:tex>
and so we write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[-i=i^{3}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[-j=j^{3}]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[-k=k^{3}]]></fr:tex>, and also
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[(-1)^{2}=1.]]></fr:tex>
We have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(-1)i=-i]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(-1)j=-j]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(-1)k=-k]]></fr:tex>.
After a bit of work, we find
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[ij=-ji=k]]></fr:tex>
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[jk=-kj=i]]></fr:tex>
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[ki=-ik=j]]></fr:tex></fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
