display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {GL}}\nolimits _{2}(\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex></fr:title><fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>13</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="alex-nelson.xml"
addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">Hungerford <fr:link
type="local"
href="hungerford-1974-algebra.xml"
addr="hungerford-1974-algebra"
title="Algebra">Algebra</fr:link> Exercise 1.2.3</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Consider the subgroup <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq \mathop {\textrm {GL}}\nolimits _{2}(\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> generated by powers and products of
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[A=\begin {pmatrix}0 & 1\\-1 & 0\end {pmatrix},\quad \hbox {and}\quad  B=\begin {pmatrix}0 & \mathrm {i}\\\mathrm {i} & 0\end {pmatrix}]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {i}^{2}=-1]]></fr:tex>. (We see <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A^{4}]]></fr:tex> is the identity matrix, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B^{4}]]></fr:tex> is the identity matrix.) Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-0016.xml"
addr="gr-0016"
title="Quaternion Group">Quaternion Group</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Q_{8}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>The isomorphism is given by sending <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\mapsto  j]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\mapsto  k]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[AB\mapsto  i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>